# Laravel Herd PHP

## When to use

- Running PHP commands with Laravel Herd on Windows
- Determining correct PHP version from composer.json
- Running Composer, Pest, PHPUnit, PHPStan, Pint with correct PHP binary
- Multiple PHP versions (8.1, 8.2, 8.3, 8.4)

## Critical Rule

- **ALWAYS check `composer.json` for the minimum PHP version before running ANY PHP command**
- Use the versioned binary (`php82.bat`, `php83.bat`) matching the project's minimum PHP requirement
- **NEVER use `php.bat` (without version)** — always use the explicit versioned binary

